This paper proposes a new model for computer vision, specifically for image labeling, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of high-order random fields, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for minimizing the energy function of the model, which suggests that it may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses synthetic and real data sets to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed model, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
